The paper discusses the use of provenance management techniques for capturing and preserving workflow information in biomedical analyses. This involves designing and implementing a provenance service that can capture, store, retrieve, and reconstruct workflow information. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), cybernetics (cs.CY), digital libraries (cs.DL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
